The decor is in dark, earthy colors, giving it a warm and cozy feeling.	Inside, the hotel feels very modern, with nice interior design and lightning, it's certainly impressive.	The only positive I can say about the hotel was that the entry way and common areas were nicely designed in a modern style.	The breakfast that comes with the hotel package is a standard European breakfast - both scrambled and boiled eggs, cold cereals and oatmeal, several types of ham, sausages, and bacon; pastries, several types of breads/rolls, butter, jam, fruits, orange juice, milk, and mineral water, all buffet style.